A five-year remembrance service will hold on Sunday for the late Mrs. Comfort Ijaduola Adeleke. The service takes place at First Baptist Church, Ilorin, Kwara State at 10am. Mrs. Adeleke was a business tycoon and a devout Christian. She was a member of First Baptist Church, Ilorin. She was the wife of the late Aaremole of Ijeruland in Ogbomoso, Oyo State, High Chief Jacob Adepoju Adeleke. The deceased is survived by children and grandchildren, among who is Dr. Olukayode Adeoye Adeleke, a senior medical officer with the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital (LASUTH). 